Oyo State Governor Seyi Makinde will today host Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, five South-West governors, monarchs and industrialists at Ilora Farm Settlement as the state commissions a cassava processing factory,  to boost high-quality food production for nationwide distribution. According to the Oyo State Agribusiness Development Agency, “Rontol Foods Factory’s Cassava processing plant at Ilora has an input capacity of 20 tonnes of cassava tubers for processing daily, and it will serve as a major processing centre for the smallholder farmers. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .